'''Baner Peran''' yw baner [[Kernow]]. Kensa deskrifans godhvedhys an baner avel baner Kernow a veu skrifys en 1838.<ref name=gilbert>[http://www.google.co.uk/books?id=oYYvAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA332&dq=formerly+the+banner+of+St.+Perran 'The Parochial History of Cornwall', gen Davies Gilbert. (1838) Vol III, p. 332]</ref> Usyes ew gen [[Kernowyon]] avel arwodh a honenieth.<ref name=rendle>[http://www.flaginstitute.org/pdfs/Phil%20Rendle.pdf Phil Rendle, Cornwall - The Mysteries of St Piran, The Flag Institute]</ref>

An baner henwys rag [[Peran]] ew krows wynn war kilva dhu. Leverys ew dre wrug Piran dowis an dhew liwyow-ma woja gweles an [[sten]] tedh ow skollya mes a'n mun du en y tan. Hemm a wrug wharvos dres y dhiskudhyans a sten e'n [[6ves kansblydhen]], ow dos ha bos tassans stenyoryon.

==Devedhyanjow==
Leverys ew dr'ujy an desin ow tos dhort kensa 1188 pan veu an baner usyes e'n [[Crowsgasow]],<ref>[http://www.celticleague.org/flags.html Celtic League flags]</ref> ha ma erthygel en Encyclopaedia Britannica ow leverel dre veu an baner degys gen an barth [[Kernowyon|Gernowek]] orth [[Cas Agincourt]] (1415).<ref>[http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/gb-corn.html Cornish flag]</ref> Bettegens, y hevel dr'ew an devyn res gen Encyclopaedia Britannica derayes gen onen a wra dos dhort bardhonek a 1590 henwys ''"Poly-Olbion"'' gen Michael Drayton. Ma'n bardhonek ow leverel dre wrug an baner degys gen an Gernowyon orth Agincourt disqwedhes dew omdowler a Gernow en colm.<ref>''Poly-Olbion'' gen Michael Drayton</ref>

An dustuny godhvedhys an moyha a-varr a'n baner-ma a veu recordyes gen Davies Gilbert en y ober 1838 'The Parochial History of Cornwall', lemma ev ow leverel a-dro dhe <blockquote>''"grows wydn war kilva dhu a veu kens obma baner Peran ha baner Kernow; dres lycklod gen nebes kampol dhe'n mun du ha'n alkan gwynn a sten"''.<ref name=gilbert/><ref name=rendle/></blockquote>

Onen a'n diskwedhyanjow an kottha a'n baner a ell bos gwelys en fenester gweder liw orth [[Westminster Abbey]]. Discudhys a veu en 1888 dhe gov an deviser hag ynjynnyor gerys da a Gernow [[Richard Trevithick]]. Ma'n fenester ow tisqwedhes [[Myhal]] orth an penn ha naw sans a Gernow, Peran, [[Petrok]], Pinnock,[http://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=5453] Jermyn, Julyan, Cyriacus, Constentyn, Nonna and [[Gerens]] a-woles. Y hevel dr'ew Pedn Peran portrayans a Trevithick y honen, ha ma ev ow ton baner Kernow.<ref>[http://www.westminster-abbey.org/our-history/people/richard-trevithick Westminster Abbey]</ref>

